article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 85, Edward Waters 49
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- C.J. Reed scored 23 points and Javois Bryant added 14 as Bethune-Cookman defeated Edward Waters 85-49 in its season opener on Saturday night. Garrius Hollomon contributed 11 points and Alexander Starling 10 for the Wildcats, whose defense limited the Tigers to a 38.2 percent shooting effort. Johnny Nelson led Edward Waters (0-4) with 20 points. No other Tiger produced more than six points, but the Tigers did win the battle of the boards, 47-34. Bethune-Cookman used a full-court pressure defense to go on runs of 14-4, 12-2 and 16-0 in the first half to take a commanding 46-23 lead at the break. Reed led the charge, collecting 17 of his points in the first half. The Wildcats, with all players getting involved, pushed the margin to 30 points, 68-38, with 10:05 to go. They coasted the rest of the way, once leading by 37 points, 81-44, with 1:51 showing.
